After settling down in Garoua ahead of their opener against Egypt on January 11 against Egypt at the 31st AFCON, Super Eagles interim coach Austin Eguavoen has admitted that he was a bit relaxed now with the team. Just as the duo of Tyrone Ebuehi and Jamilu Collins will today team up with the squad in Cameroon from bases in Italy and Germany. Eguavoen who lamented the inability of Odion Ighalo to join the team is confident that the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) is working hard to ensure the 2019 AFCON highest goal scorer hook up with the team in Cameroon.   Eagles holds first session in Garoua     Ighalo out of AFCON 2021     An interminable path to nationhood   “First game is very crucial to any team in any major competition; I will say there was a little bit of pressure but I think I am more relaxed now than two weeks ago,” he admitted. Already, Eguavoen said he had lined up some strikers that would replace Ighalo but he was stopped following the decision by CAF not to allow last-minute replacement which they argued would only be possible through injury. - Advertisement - He, however, expressed optimism that NFF would continue to work with Ighalo in ensuring that the former Watford striker team up with the squad in Cameroon.